.TH OZMA 1 "2024" "1.0.0" "ozmaos"
.SH NAME
ozma \\- OzmaOS management CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ozma
[\\fIOPTIONS\\fR] \\fICOMMAND\\fR [\\fIARGS\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ozma
is the command-line management interface for OzmaOS. It provides system health monitoring,
update management, service control, and Ozma Connect integration.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B ozma status
Display system health summary including controller status, services, network,
ZFS pools, and storage usage.
.TP
.B ozma update [\\fB--check\\fR] [\\fB--apply\\fR]
Check for and apply operating system and controller updates.
.TP
.B ozma service enable \\fINAME\\fR
Enable and start a managed service.
.TP
.B ozma service disable \\fINAME\\fR
Disable and stop a managed service.
.TP
.B ozma service restart \\fINAME\\fR
Restart a managed service.
.TP
.B ozma connect link \\fIEMAIL\\fR
Link the controller to an Ozma Connect account.
.TP
.B ozma connect unlink
Unlink the controller from Ozma Connect.
.TP
.B ozma connect status
Show Ozma Connect relay and backup status.
.TP
.B ozma logs [\\fISERVICE\\fR]
Display logs for a service (defaults to ozma-controller).
.TP
.B ozma backup now
Trigger an immediate encrypted backup to Ozma Connect.
.TP
.B ozma zfs status
Display ZFS pool health and scrub status.
.TP
.B ozma diagnose [\\fB--output FILE\\fR]
Run health checks and create a gzipped support bundle.
.SH MANAGED SERVICES
The following services can be managed:
.IR frigate ,
.IR vaultwarden ,
.IR parsec ,
.IR tailscale ,
.IR nginx ,
.IR ozma-controller ,
.IR ozma-node .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \\fB--version\\fR
Show the program version and exit.
.TP
.B \\fB--help\\fR
Show this help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/ozma/
OzmaOS data directory.
.TP
.I /etc/ozma/
OzmaOS configuration directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/ozma/
User-specific OzmaOS configuration.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check system status:
.B ozma status
.TP
Check for updates without applying:
.B ozma update --check
.TP
Enable Frigate service:
.B ozma service enable frigate
.TP
Create a support bundle:
.B ozma diagnose --output /tmp/support-bundle.tar.gz
